<hr local-id=3D"e8588833-2a62-4110-bed9-e6bf919d2e35">
<h2 local-id=3D"cd61180c8d68" id=3D"Task15-RAD-1.5Overview">1.5 Overview</h=
2>
<p local-id=3D"91b7942ab5d3">This document is organized into the following =
sections:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"a08fdfe5-fcc6-469f-897a-bdb18dbeb6bd">
<li local-id=3D"512ddce9-c605-4307-aa6d-fba3258d4b4c">
<p local-id=3D"de3566a3c9d1"><strong>Project Overview</strong> =E2=80=93 ex=
plains project goals and background</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"f7a10cf8-6940-4c67-bbc2-58d78114fc4c">
<p local-id=3D"69e16a6bf96a"><strong>Functional Requirements</strong> =E2=
=80=93 describes system features and use cases</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"4b5c19c5-19f4-457f-8ebc-aff6cb25847d">
<p local-id=3D"89b07a0efc36"><strong>Non-Functional Requirements</strong> =
=E2=80=93 defines system quality requirements</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"e46940ca-ce0a-4bb6-9051-2ff8632002eb">
<p local-id=3D"880739f4d799"><strong>Risk Analysis</strong> =E2=80=93 ident=
ifies possible risks and mitigation strategies</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"0185b210-4c19-4e3f-a28f-893f9fa622c1">
<p local-id=3D"6e1a25af85bd"><strong>Glossary and Appendices</strong> =E2=
=80=93 provide additional information</p></li>
</ul>
<hr local-id=3D"663f1935-83c2-42c0-bf42-2862ac9c23a8">
<h1 local-id=3D"0fa8cac5b496" id=3D"Task15-RAD-2.ProjectOverview">2. Projec=
t Overview</h1>
<h2 local-id=3D"29fc5fc21c9d" id=3D"Task15-RAD-2.1ProjectObjectives">2.1 Pr=
oject Objectives</h2>
<p local-id=3D"7be8aaa702ce">The main objective of this project is to imple=
ment <strong>secure web communication using HTTPS on an Nginx web server</s=
trong>.</p>
<p local-id=3D"fa3cb807de27">Key objectives include:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"bc24fd83-2057-4e0b-b575-b758419fb639">
<li local-id=3D"0f3528d3-5ba4-469e-a11e-c98514685b30">
<p local-id=3D"233c2ca42898">Enable <strong>SSL/TLS encryption</strong></p>=
</li>
<li local-id=3D"8049c157-c22b-4ba0-9046-36e22e12b9d3">
<p local-id=3D"d6b42a663fd5">Implement <strong>HTTP to HTTPS automatic redi=
rection</strong></p></li>
<li local-id=3D"cb6efcbe-446a-424c-88e4-29618a3913ee">
<p local-id=3D"b9e5c6e1e817">Configure <strong>basic security headers</stro=
ng></p></li>
<li local-id=3D"6e9942ce-423c-4ac3-8d45-140f2c233fb7">
<p local-id=3D"edde720d3fb4">Ensure secure access to web resources</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"bd96056c-9a3d-4e96-ae47-e2fcd3a343c9">
<p local-id=3D"abca54a61094">Validate the configuration through testing</p>=
</li>
</ul>
<hr local-id=3D"4767934d-a32e-458f-9c68-318dc7fbad60">
<h2 local-id=3D"055b061aa1a4" id=3D"Task15-RAD-2.2BusinessGoals">2.2 Busine=
ss Goals</h2>
<p local-id=3D"cfcdce95dfee">This project aims to achieve the following bus=
iness goals:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"4d8eaa17-07c4-413a-9be6-85a5d7702de2">
<li local-id=3D"e26a7b69-7b51-47f9-a36e-1fcf861aab6f">
<p local-id=3D"8096b10c7fbf">Improve <strong>web security</strong></p></li>
<li local-id=3D"92ec7318-5ad8-4293-bd3a-8395861707b1">
<p local-id=3D"41da04292f94">Protect user data during transmission</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"8c08cc55-1b78-4818-bd21-3841a692378d">
<p local-id=3D"71d24db9bafe">Build <strong>trust with secure connections</s=
trong></p></li>
<li local-id=3D"5081b79f-6f23-4ef7-a622-11b2fbb9d039">
<p local-id=3D"d08aa23ede43">Follow <strong>industry-standard web security =
practices</strong></p></li>
<li local-id=3D"4cf03b61-6b36-437b-a40d-94ce545d2e52">
<p local-id=3D"32130380dfd4">Prepare infrastructure for <strong>production-=
grade deployment</strong></p></li>
</ul>
<hr local-id=3D"d9981e02-a6f0-4e81-9baa-53ec08d37786">
<h2 local-id=3D"47cb9c200433" id=3D"Task15-RAD-2.3Background">2.3 Backgroun=
d</h2>
<p local-id=3D"87bfada93081">Modern web applications require <strong>secure=
 communication channels</strong> to protect sensitive data from interceptio=
n.</p>
<p local-id=3D"26130d100c9e">By default, HTTP communication is <strong>not =
encrypted</strong>, making it vulnerable to attacks such as:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"d72b0580-4cf4-46c3-a944-c413358da88f">
<li local-id=3D"38defc96-b981-4caf-b9a9-99a508c9cda7">
<p local-id=3D"ead4103d2c2e">Man-in-the-middle attacks</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"1241cf67-331a-4964-8758-037da1bfe738">
<p local-id=3D"fdee442f605d">Data interception</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"17ee8415-2442-4d09-80ca-7277c74d7846">
<p local-id=3D"fa4e038fc415">Session hijacking</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"1c924f87517d">To address these issues, this project implemen=
ts <strong>HTTPS encryption using SSL/TLS on the Nginx web server</strong>.=
</p>
<hr local-id=3D"dc25277d-a47a-45a3-b863-d65598bc6059">
<h2 local-id=3D"867c35ee6c9a" id=3D"Task15-RAD-2.4Constraints">2.4 Constrai=
nts</h2>
<p local-id=3D"0dd0037033d1">The following constraints apply to this implem=
entation:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"dd877cbc-ecbe-48d9-8065-87c2bf60ef74">
<li local-id=3D"c6f2b193-deaf-46e4-9d71-b1d203c9b612">
<p local-id=3D"17cc99f305a8">Self-signed certificates are used instead of C=
A-issued certificates</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"cd038dd6-0323-460a-8d12-175b41b2ad38">
<p local-id=3D"ff559e63f439">Implementation is performed on a <strong>singl=
e Linux server</strong></p></li>
<li local-id=3D"743f5e50-7bad-43cd-838f-36ff2278bd15">
<p local-id=3D"e921c9b4167f">Limited project time (approx. 2 hours)</p></li=
>
<li local-id=3D"faf222e7-4803-46a1-9785-7603253e675a">
<p local-id=3D"6ee10fc581d5">No external automation tools used</p></li>
</ul>
<hr local-id=3D"0df97e60-1f1c-4e72-92a2-4d82b62d033c">
<h1 local-id=3D"4acd9fcd166e" id=3D"Task15-RAD-3.FunctionalRequirements">3.=
 Functional Requirements</h1>
<h2 local-id=3D"86402076f352" id=3D"Task15-RAD-3.1UseCaseDiagram">3.1 Use C=
ase Diagram</h2>
<p local-id=3D"364c31194653">The following use case diagram represents the =
interactions between users and the system.</p><span class=3D"confluence-emb=
edded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size"><i=
mg class=3D"confluence-embedded-image image-center" alt=3D"Untitled Diagram=
.drawio (14)-20260312-070639.png" width=3D"468" loading=3D"lazy" src=3D"471=
9e1c9c1021f563e6fd8c9bee6fe6362cb0d53433c93f54e19aed1d22fbc43" data-image-s=
rc=3D"https://iamops.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1853423632/Unt=
itled%20Diagram.drawio%20(14)-20260312-070639.png?version=3D1&amp;modificat=
ionDate=3D1773299347496&amp;cacheVersion=3D1&amp;api=3Dv2" data-height=3D"4=
41" data-width=3D"1011" data-unresolved-comment-count=3D"0" data-linked-res=
ource-id=3D"1855619351" data-linked-resource-version=3D"1" data-linked-reso=
urce-type=3D"attachment" data-linked-resource-default-alias=3D"Untitled Dia=
gram.drawio (14)-20260312-070639.png" data-base-url=3D"https://iamops.atlas=
sian.net/wiki" data-linked-resource-content-type=3D"image/png" data-linked-=
resource-container-id=3D"1853423632" data-linked-resource-container-version=
=3D"1" data-media-id=3D"90d3e7c4-828e-4293-9801-5ebb3edac935" data-media-ty=
pe=3D"file" height=3D"204"></span>
<p local-id=3D"0ca4cae26833">Actors:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"a1a97424-1d23-43a9-8ca8-369cfba82955">
<li local-id=3D"d6d1a004-2ff5-48f3-8fa9-565ca2899e3b">
<p local-id=3D"c950530bc5eb">User (Client Browser)</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"bf6b2c08-144d-4d2e-a620-2f79b2efce27">
<p local-id=3D"b365eb636fe5">DevOps Engineer</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"bf33c638-3bf2-4b6a-aa67-3fa798479feb">
<p local-id=3D"ffd240b16e56">Nginx Web Server</p></li>
</ul>
<hr local-id=3D"5f05f8f4-a36c-4caa-902d-a3f9e0cd96a6">
<h1 local-id=3D"4b9fdfecda40" id=3D"Task15-RAD-3.2UseCases">3.2 Use Cases</=
h1>
<hr local-id=3D"0bb8d17d-2558-49ef-b2d8-1eeb4ea0c988">
<h1 local-id=3D"1964f7d64b99" id=3D"Task15-RAD-3.2.1UseCase1:InstallNginxWe=
bServer">3.2.1 Use Case 1: Install Nginx Web Server</h1>
<h3 local-id=3D"76f3d6058e7a" id=3D"Task15-RAD-Description">Description</h3=
>
<p local-id=3D"958896ea0d77">This use case describes the process of install=
ing and verifying the Nginx web server on a Linux system.</p>
<h3 local-id=3D"edf6dc34bb70" id=3D"Task15-RAD-Actors">Actors</h3>
<p local-id=3D"f4d8b04c06e8">DevOps Engineer</p>
<h3 local-id=3D"9297c7158f18" id=3D"Task15-RAD-Preconditions">Preconditions=
</h3>
<ul local-id=3D"9efd5dbb-49a8-4020-adb4-73eeb65ec895">
<li local-id=3D"3494a417-b5af-4b98-ad04-2c2d70ea9731">
<p local-id=3D"2f3d249fef30">Linux server is available</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"41e5a124-9d2b-4d96-9ee5-55866e04d67e">
<p local-id=3D"f980a5592522">Internet connectivity exists</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"0607469e-40bb-4794-a1ce-825d7f2ee36e">
<p local-id=3D"53a90a97741e">User has sudo privileges</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 local-id=3D"3d61cab23e3a" id=3D"Task15-RAD-Postconditions">Postconditio=
ns</h3>
<ul local-id=3D"2ab78b9e-f552-4ada-8b4c-71a21be5217c">
<li local-id=3D"858d0f15-bb24-4757-af03-31df06e487c8">
<p local-id=3D"1bf5a772c87a">Nginx is successfully installed and running</p=
></li>
</ul>
<h3 local-id=3D"b51fe5e98378" id=3D"Task15-RAD-FlowofEvents">Flow of Events=
</h3>
<ol start=3D"1" local-id=3D"af501c32-fa0a-458d-b873-a4bc4f4dcf2d">
<li local-id=3D"dea2246a-935c-49d9-843f-d7b6181ddcf4">
<p local-id=3D"49142cebf80b">DevOps engineer updates package repository.</p=
></li>
<li local-id=3D"9535fcea-f82b-4be4-9851-94b60eec8059">
<p local-id=3D"db8b5c84348d">Nginx is installed using the package manager.<=
/p></li>
<li local-id=3D"06bf00d4-06a4-4e30-8868-903b851318d6">
<p local-id=3D"35ee40dc3d75">Nginx service is started.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"612b3a89-c26f-4b68-93ae-14793473eec7">
<p local-id=3D"9fa1e16284cf">Service status is verified.</p></li>
</ol>
<h3 local-id=3D"73f58e030caa" id=3D"Task15-RAD-AlternativeFlows">Alternativ=
e Flows</h3>
<ul local-id=3D"8d826ef1-2f9d-4db9-b364-815822d14611">
<li local-id=3D"0d95c3b7-d3c9-49ab-8039-242bbfa9d864">
<p local-id=3D"6d7ecb5ad579">Installation fails due to network issues.</p><=
/li>
<li local-id=3D"56cc4cab-9a89-439c-b99c-eaa5d68ac2df">
<p local-id=3D"2076d552711b">Insufficient permissions prevent installation.=
</p></li>
</ul>
<hr local-id=3D"3eab4bc3-9be8-4833-9ee5-9fbb25b49637">
<h1 local-id=3D"d70c42db9981" id=3D"Task15-RAD-3.2.2UseCase2:GenerateSSLCer=
tificate">3.2.2 Use Case 2: Generate SSL Certificate</h1>
<h3 local-id=3D"e46d1d7a8d94" id=3D"Task15-RAD-Description.1">Description</=
h3>
<p local-id=3D"74ed4defadde">This use case describes generating a self-sign=
ed SSL certificate for HTTPS communication.</p>
<h3 local-id=3D"4b16549e0d2e" id=3D"Task15-RAD-Actors.1">Actors</h3>
<p local-id=3D"be8445170f0d">DevOps Engineer</p>
<h3 local-id=3D"bba181970afd" id=3D"Task15-RAD-Preconditions.1">Preconditio=
ns</h3>
<ul local-id=3D"964e2ef0-fd07-41e3-b563-5a222eb25e1f">
<li local-id=3D"feba3a50-55d5-4d88-8c6d-d5a9e0f9f6bf">
<p local-id=3D"f779fa95e558">Nginx server installed</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"e300ac0f-bdff-4d1c-847d-3085c01a6122">
<p local-id=3D"a4a1c7770d81">OpenSSL available</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 local-id=3D"a0291c11ba36" id=3D"Task15-RAD-Postconditions.1">Postcondit=
ions</h3>
<ul local-id=3D"f405b779-613a-45cb-9ce5-767ba0f95f24">
<li local-id=3D"764a85c7-7999-4539-aff4-35066713d5cb">
<p local-id=3D"e619fb0e9586">SSL certificate and private key are created</p=
></li>
</ul>
<h3 local-id=3D"e5a1bc8146c4" id=3D"Task15-RAD-FlowofEvents.1">Flow of Even=
ts</h3>
<ol start=3D"1" local-id=3D"6f77e00a-2560-4eb2-bdc0-4d0a91057731">
<li local-id=3D"70b7d09b-58b3-4f81-a4c4-fdb591668c65">
<p local-id=3D"0b77f66c35e4">DevOps engineer creates SSL directory.</p></li=
>
<li local-id=3D"d6f5d51b-39ef-406a-a1e1-a7048691ceb4">
<p local-id=3D"1e9e651a20b2">OpenSSL generates certificate and private key.=
</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"4c30baa1-a023-4b47-a403-3511140ff699">
<p local-id=3D"383ecef3fbe5">Certificate files are stored in <code>/etc/ngi=
nx/ssl</code>.</p></li>
</ol>
<h3 local-id=3D"4b21c08fd64d" id=3D"Task15-RAD-AlternativeFlows.1">Alternat=
ive Flows</h3>
<ul local-id=3D"b8460f02-f07b-49d8-acea-4a4f6d146f0d">
<li local-id=3D"cb5c1aae-2c56-4f07-bfbe-9e48493ea461">
<p local-id=3D"a4278e545fc5">OpenSSL command fails due to incorrect paramet=
ers.</p></li>
</ul>
<hr local-id=3D"7d9f244c-185e-4f5c-b0a1-796e442cc4e3">
<h1 local-id=3D"18ff7058ce94" id=3D"Task15-RAD-3.2.3UseCase3:ConfigureHTTPS=
inNginx">3.2.3 Use Case 3: Configure HTTPS in Nginx</h1>
<h3 local-id=3D"6d00caab0399" id=3D"Task15-RAD-Description.2">Description</=
h3>
<p local-id=3D"2ea1e3d1ba73">This use case describes configuring Nginx to e=
nable HTTPS and redirect HTTP traffic.</p>
<h3 local-id=3D"17b591c2bd76" id=3D"Task15-RAD-Actors.2">Actors</h3>
<p local-id=3D"bb633c07c947">DevOps Engineer</p>
<h3 local-id=3D"62c4485ad47f" id=3D"Task15-RAD-Preconditions.2">Preconditio=
ns</h3>
<ul local-id=3D"eeb0661a-dd0c-4198-827f-b6071cf0ca4d">
<li local-id=3D"ada5b203-e947-4671-968d-35ff1d5ccf8a">
<p local-id=3D"c4f9ec591e03">SSL certificate exists</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"302d4bf5-ca88-4b93-bf48-31f0698a3c6d">
<p local-id=3D"c8db5d5d6476">Nginx installed</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 local-id=3D"25e1b7fca23f" id=3D"Task15-RAD-Postconditions.2">Postcondit=
ions</h3>
<ul local-id=3D"8a110bb8-6062-4f9e-b81d-ce91d29526d9">
<li local-id=3D"355c8e2c-d292-4c28-b6c9-6f910847f5ae">
<p local-id=3D"1284b302ff17">Nginx serves content over HTTPS</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 local-id=3D"ecb3b8c77c97" id=3D"Task15-RAD-FlowofEvents.2">Flow of Even=
ts</h3>
<ol start=3D"1" local-id=3D"387c1275-32e2-4f26-aa1f-c48adec508c3">
<li local-id=3D"cb931ad0-3b5c-4149-ac65-f4a2c805dc4b">
<p local-id=3D"3673e3ef7efe">DevOps engineer edits Nginx configuration file=
.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"f12a71c6-3568-4147-aa34-22e96038c326">
<p local-id=3D"0425bc860fb5">SSL certificate path is added.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"58a870f5-83a8-4592-be0e-d2f155f6c91e">
<p local-id=3D"f9cb3dd197d3">HTTPS listener is configured.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"41c24769-463a-4b44-b35b-322c9378f868">
<p local-id=3D"58737a45130d">HTTP redirect rule is added.</p></li>
</ol>
<h3 local-id=3D"8a95a5ce3e29" id=3D"Task15-RAD-AlternativeFlows.2">Alternat=
ive Flows</h3>
<ul local-id=3D"58da470f-b227-4701-a876-70e349e92b72">
<li local-id=3D"d0c66a27-b85f-4c9a-b408-21a14f81c48a">
<p local-id=3D"be3bf4ff6627">Configuration errors detected during validatio=
n.</p></li>
</ul>
<hr local-id=3D"aa0464f9-b508-426d-83b6-1977ce3c4a92">
<h1 local-id=3D"2bdc717c9982" id=3D"Task15-RAD-3.2.4UseCase4:ValidateSecure=
ServerConfiguration">3.2.4 Use Case 4: Validate Secure Server Configuration=
</h1>
<h3 local-id=3D"428af98d27d7" id=3D"Task15-RAD-Description.3">Description</=
h3>
<p local-id=3D"3252c0e49cf2">This use case verifies that HTTPS and security=
 headers are working correctly.</p>
<h3 local-id=3D"211f9c42f2e6" id=3D"Task15-RAD-Actors.3">Actors</h3>
<p local-id=3D"e33e8c4f5b43">User, DevOps Engineer</p>
<h3 local-id=3D"34c562c6a778" id=3D"Task15-RAD-Preconditions.3">Preconditio=
ns</h3>
<ul local-id=3D"90a11328-c72d-4ba3-8e07-8b412bb7132f">
<li local-id=3D"8360650e-3202-44a9-a63b-b66704e40b4e">
<p local-id=3D"d5c6bc96a475">Server configuration completed</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 local-id=3D"0d6fff36fd61" id=3D"Task15-RAD-Postconditions.3">Postcondit=
ions</h3>
<ul local-id=3D"8f1bf2aa-1181-4ca6-9524-4935864121ef">
<li local-id=3D"18bdb724-c475-489a-8a6d-890a1f19e5b3">
<p local-id=3D"bd4e99d1d200">HTTPS access verified</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"5c9352ca-c162-4771-9c32-83788a5c4308">
<p local-id=3D"277246de092a">Security headers confirmed</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 local-id=3D"745f6c3ad38e" id=3D"Task15-RAD-FlowofEvents.3">Flow of Even=
ts</h3>
<ol start=3D"1" local-id=3D"8b37b77d-41ed-4dbb-afcc-a5495098b967">
<li local-id=3D"be8582db-9964-4f5b-8bc5-7d7feae00e33">
<p local-id=3D"cdbb531bf68c">User accesses server via browser.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"4ef50b12-a019-4f9d-84e9-d37c41f1824a">
<p local-id=3D"667f8dd30453">HTTPS connection is established.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"66690ca7-d56a-4ff6-b3a8-5a533dc546b1">
<p local-id=3D"af889ee4b58b">DevOps engineer runs curl command to verify he=
aders.</p></li>
</ol>
<h3 local-id=3D"6b03474609bc" id=3D"Task15-RAD-AlternativeFlows.3">Alternat=
ive Flows</h3>
<ul local-id=3D"7fc65ae3-657d-4f04-b143-66a5873155d8">
<li local-id=3D"46fb89e0-aaeb-4a3b-961f-97ef6573a0da">
<p local-id=3D"c1a5f3787cb4">Browser displays certificate warning due to se=
lf-signed certificate.</p></li>
</ul>
<hr local-id=3D"b84ab0b1-6531-4bfa-a9b2-d29319fd9d66">
<h1 local-id=3D"d58b1ed4d8fd" id=3D"Task15-RAD-4.Non-FunctionalRequirements=
">4. Non-Functional Requirements</h1>
<h2 local-id=3D"42ff5f6f9550" id=3D"Task15-RAD-4.1PerformanceRequirements">=
4.1 Performance Requirements</h2>
<ul local-id=3D"d98db58c-9456-48d4-b152-b1434393a482">
<li local-id=3D"f6c76b66-df0e-4350-b2d2-d144e9338056">
<p local-id=3D"d3e1fca38736">Server should respond to requests within <stro=
ng>2 seconds</strong>.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"7a1b6136-76a4-46ff-8d96-e1ab0310662f">
<p local-id=3D"5abe66c180cd">Nginx should handle multiple concurrent connec=
tions efficiently.</p></li>
</ul>
<hr local-id=3D"4fe08cc8-d8ab-4a8a-aafa-990da1424b38">
<h2 local-id=3D"41c8de0c7f54" id=3D"Task15-RAD-4.2SecurityRequirements">4.2=
 Security Requirements</h2>
<p local-id=3D"70fcfa61d04c">The system must ensure:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"025fcbb6-cdf0-4d9a-b3da-9c3b98e9852d">
<li local-id=3D"97214bbf-4597-4b72-81b8-9f1b2ebb50c3">
<p local-id=3D"25f28564ca6c">HTTPS encryption</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"c82c9130-680c-4fd0-9f5e-d21d1f0ff5aa">
<p local-id=3D"9d26c1f69289">Secure SSL certificate storage</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"98b91251-dc17-4434-ad56-8431b2021a05">
<p local-id=3D"ec8d8c81e42e">HTTP =E2=86=92 HTTPS redirection</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"cd10c16f-a270-401c-b21e-849c8901bb55">
<p local-id=3D"0b53a75c40a4">Security headers enabled</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"21880fd38153">Headers implemented:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"0c2fb866-8b28-4270-83b9-ece6e8b41955">
<li local-id=3D"9dbba616-98cb-4dc9-a451-b31d291c0c2c">
<p local-id=3D"87324432439a">X-Frame-Options</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"e106d7d8-f668-4d02-8484-7841cc1fbbb5">
<p local-id=3D"941ed9cc8702">X-Content-Type-Options</p></li>
</ul>
<hr local-id=3D"0b17417e-7b7f-4a55-b6cb-c1dc1a80c699">
<h2 local-id=3D"6a2bb58e7832" id=3D"Task15-RAD-4.3UsabilityRequirements">4.=
3 Usability Requirements</h2>
<ul local-id=3D"75055634-6947-4f76-942b-94b19966e4aa">
<li local-id=3D"35cd22d1-b015-4d4e-94ff-b497cbde7c65">
<p local-id=3D"762200ea1ad9">System configuration should be easy for admini=
strators to manage.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"5f6783f9-bb91-4083-bee5-8f39a9936e61">
<p local-id=3D"ba0a1dee32f9">Server status should be verifiable through sim=
ple commands.</p></li>
</ul>
<hr local-id=3D"aec4be3e-34f1-40cd-958a-d992f73c04cd">
<h2 local-id=3D"60087c037884" id=3D"Task15-RAD-4.4ReliabilityRequirements">=
4.4 Reliability Requirements</h2>
<ul local-id=3D"a837049c-e2a6-4899-8579-f01cfb9e0748">
<li local-id=3D"bea75549-489b-46c9-9b20-582196c49018">
<p local-id=3D"7657f1224d9a">Nginx service should remain operational with <=
strong>high uptime</strong>.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"5cdf9cc2-0e53-436b-ad86-716ed15cc872">
<p local-id=3D"c4045d8440f4">Configuration validation should prevent incorr=
ect deployment.</p></li>
</ul>
<hr local-id=3D"099b3714-4d08-4924-8d0f-d678619fe5fe">
<h2 local-id=3D"661971cc2149" id=3D"Task15-RAD-4.5ComplianceRequirements">4=
.5 Compliance Requirements</h2>
<p local-id=3D"eee7fac98e4a">This implementation follows common <strong>web=
 security best practices</strong> such as enforcing HTTPS communication.</p=
>
<p local-id=3D"0116e4f2bf33">Formal regulatory compliance requirements are =
<strong>not applicable for this implementation</strong>.</p>
<hr local-id=3D"61f622a4-ec66-4bc1-8dd2-4e613d1a31f8">
<h1 local-id=3D"5d64ba8b69c3" id=3D"Task15-RAD-5.AssumptionsandDependencies=
">5. Assumptions and Dependencies</h1>
<h2 local-id=3D"c8cec1801892" id=3D"Task15-RAD-5.1Assumptions">5.1 Assumpti=
ons</h2>
<ul local-id=3D"1877e165-4253-478a-af91-8f5274fce4c6">
<li local-id=3D"f4f80116-0b46-4dcc-b1d0-368d344ab4a0">
<p local-id=3D"df6198cdec92">Linux server is available</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"c3bc4835-79a7-4b13-8ef1-e82bcd39b132">
<p local-id=3D"10050ed9ec38">Nginx is installed via package manager</p></li=
>
<li local-id=3D"3bf8568e-d2da-4ef2-b955-fea8ed2f166c">
<p local-id=3D"2c68b03d8213">DevOps engineer has administrative privileges<=
/p></li>
</ul>
